mg src=http://c2a.penguintek.net/fubar/skull2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Greatest video game EVER!!</span><hr size=1> An avid console gamer and import gamer here is my list of favorite games in a top 10 fashion:<br>
<br>
1) Radiant Silvergun (Sega Saturn, Do yourself a favor and play this game before you die)<br>
2) Castlevania: SotN (Sega Saturn, was also nice on the PSX but the Saturn version had 2 extra characters to play and 2 extra parts of the castle)<br>
3) Final Fantasy VII (PSX, nuff said)<br>
4) Final Fantasy III (SNES, nuff said)<br>
5) Guardian Heroes (Sega Saturn, role playing + beat'em up + fighting game)<br>
6) Soul Calibur (DC)<br>
7) Garou: Mark of the Wolves (Neo-Geo)<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Metal Gear Solid (PSX, nuff said)<br>
9) Marvel vs. Capcom 2 (DC, insanity inside a little cd case)<br>
10) Star Wars: Rogue Squadron (N64, yes i loved this game and the new one looks incredible)<br>
<br>
Thats my top 10. The near 200 dollars to purchase Radiant Silvergun from places like eBay, etc. is worth it. Never have I played a game with some much skill, insanity, and pure adrenaline rushes than this game. Like a natural high everytime you play it. <p><br>
