<br>
1) WASTELAND (Greatest game EVER!)<br>
<br>
2) EQ (DAOC is cool but doubt I'll be able to go 2 years like I did with that game)<br>
<br>
3) Warcraft (Started an genre)<br>
<br>
4) Ultima (Not a fan of the games but definatly ground breaking)<br>
<br>
5) Sims (It's so existential to sit there playing a computer game where your guy is sitting there playing a computer game&lt;I wonder if he's making his guy sit there and play a computer game?&gt;)<br>
<br>
6) Might and Magic (Xeen I felt was one of the best of this series) <br>
<br>
7) Masters of Magic (If you haven't played this game go get it from an abandonware site) (This game is better than Master of Orion btw)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Doom (I hate FPS's but this game defined a genre (but wasn't the first of it's kind that honor goes to Wolfenstein))<br>
<br>
9) Test Drive (One of the earliest racing sims and while not so hot today the earlier versions were def. a benchmark)<br>
<br>
10) MS Flight Sim (Again not really my genre but WOW it's realistic)<br>
